WEBVTT

00:00.800 --> 00:02.467
♪♪

00:02.502 --> 00:03.702
Morning, Pinkie Pie.

00:03.737 --> 00:06.438
Get your Ponyville
Chronicle right here!

00:06.473 --> 00:07.739
Fan-tizzy-astic!

00:11.244 --> 00:14.112
I just love to read about happy
happenings and it's always good

00:14.147 --> 00:16.815
to be a pony in
the know, you know?

00:16.850 --> 00:19.718
And there's so much to know!

00:19.753 --> 00:23.121
Seems like a bunch of
boring hooey to me.

00:23.156 --> 00:25.557
Does "NEW SHRUBBERY
IN CASTLE GARDEN"!

00:25.592 --> 00:27.559
sound like boring
hooey to you?

00:27.594 --> 00:29.628
Snooze.

00:29.663 --> 00:31.229
What about...

00:31.264 --> 00:34.232
"PARASPRITE INFESTATION IN
FILLYDELPHIA ERADICATED"?

00:34.267 --> 00:36.635
That's great news!

00:36.670 --> 00:41.573
Another day, another
parasprite hype story.

00:41.608 --> 00:44.242
Noodles named official
food of Whinnyapolis!

00:44.277 --> 00:46.545
Author A.K. Yearling
announces retirement!

00:46.580 --> 00:48.413
Cloudsdale election
heating up for candidate

00:48.448 --> 00:49.548
in favor of
cooling it down!

00:49.583 --> 00:51.716
WHAT? Let me see that!

00:51.751 --> 00:54.786
I never knew you were so
into politics, Rainbow.

00:54.821 --> 00:56.788
No, this!

00:56.823 --> 00:59.357
It CAN'T be true...

00:59.392 --> 01:01.259
I'd have never have picked
noodles as the official food

01:01.294 --> 01:02.360
of Whinnyapolis, either.

01:02.395 --> 01:04.196
But here we are!

01:04.231 --> 01:05.597
No, Pinkie!

01:05.632 --> 01:06.765
I can't believe...

01:06.800 --> 01:08.433
that the greatest author...

01:08.468 --> 01:11.169
and secret pony
adventurer of all time...

01:11.204 --> 01:14.473
A.K. Yearling... is retiring!

01:18.411 --> 01:21.746
♪ My little pony,
my little pony ♪

01:21.781 --> 01:23.682
♪ Aaaahhh ♪

01:23.717 --> 01:25.750
♪ My little Pony ♪

01:25.785 --> 01:28.320
♪ I used to wonder what
friendship could be. ♪

01:28.355 --> 01:30.222
♪ My Little Pony ♪

01:30.257 --> 01:32.624
♪ Until you all shared
its magic with me. ♪

01:32.659 --> 01:34.693
♪ Big adventure! ♪
♪ Tons of fun ♪

01:34.728 --> 01:36.828
♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪
Faithful and strong! ♪

01:36.863 --> 01:39.197
♪ Sharing kindness ♪
♪ it's an easy feat ♪

01:39.232 --> 01:41.199
♪ And magic makes it
all complete! ♪

01:41.234 --> 01:43.301
♪ To have my little pony ♪

01:43.336 --> 01:46.638
♪ Do you know you're all
my very best friends? ♪

01:46.673 --> 01:48.540
♪♪

01:53.847 --> 01:57.582
A.K. Yearling just
retired, like, today.

01:57.617 --> 01:59.518
Are you sure she wants visitors?

01:59.553 --> 02:02.387
Pinkie, the A.K. Yearling
I know would never quit

02:02.422 --> 02:04.156
and retire out of the blue!

02:04.191 --> 02:05.624
Something could
be really wrong

02:05.659 --> 02:07.759
and we need to make
sure she's OK.

02:07.794 --> 02:08.494
OK!

02:09.563 --> 02:11.796
Hey, you're not just trying
to make sure she writes

02:11.831 --> 02:14.699
more Daring Do
books, are you?

02:14.734 --> 02:16.668
Of course not!

02:16.703 --> 02:18.303
But that wouldn't
hurt either.

02:18.338 --> 02:19.304
Now, come on!

02:20.540 --> 02:21.773
[fast knocking]

02:23.677 --> 02:26.278
Uh, maybe she's not home.

02:26.313 --> 02:28.380
Maybe she went to the
editor-in-chief of the

02:28.415 --> 02:30.282
Ponyville Chronicle to
correct the misprint

02:30.317 --> 02:30.882
they've made!

02:30.917 --> 02:32.217
Nope. She's home.

02:32.252 --> 02:33.451
How do you know?

02:33.486 --> 02:34.619
Because she's right there...

02:34.654 --> 02:36.288
looking all sad and alone.

02:36.323 --> 02:37.589
I knew it.

02:37.624 --> 02:39.191
Something is wrong!

02:39.226 --> 02:40.525
A.K!

02:40.560 --> 02:42.794
Now she's sighing with
the weight of the world.

02:42.829 --> 02:45.564
Now she's hanging her
head in utter despair!

02:45.599 --> 02:47.632
Now she's shaking her hoof
and cursing the heavens

02:47.667 --> 02:49.668
like nothing could ever
possibly be the same again!

02:49.703 --> 02:51.703
Why oh why did this
happen to her?

02:51.738 --> 02:52.604
What?

02:52.639 --> 02:53.905
Whoops.

02:53.940 --> 02:56.775
Never mind, that time
she was just stretching.

02:56.810 --> 03:00.845
A.K., it's us! Rainbow
Dash and Pinkie Pie!

03:00.880 --> 03:02.280
Your friends!

03:02.315 --> 03:09.454
♪♪

03:09.489 --> 03:11.823
Oh, no. Did somepony ransack
your cottage again

03:11.858 --> 03:13.825
and steal some ancient
mysterious relic

03:13.860 --> 03:15.760
that's the key to saving
all of Equestria?

03:15.795 --> 03:17.929
Oooh! Sparky!

03:17.964 --> 03:18.830
[gasp]

03:20.367 --> 03:21.800
[relieved sigh]

03:21.835 --> 03:24.236
Nothing's been stolen.

03:24.271 --> 03:27.405
Then is somepony blackmailing
you and forcing you to retire?

03:27.440 --> 03:28.940
Cause if they are...

03:28.975 --> 03:32.244
No. Nothing like that.

03:32.279 --> 03:34.946
So you're just quitting
and moving away?

03:34.981 --> 03:38.683
WHY. WOULD. YOU. DO. THAT?

03:38.718 --> 03:41.920
I already explained everything
to the Ponyville Chronicle.

03:41.955 --> 03:43.922
Oh, really?

03:43.957 --> 03:46.625
"Author A.K. Yearling
announced yesterday

03:46.660 --> 03:49.561
that the next adventure novel
in her popular series,

03:49.596 --> 03:51.896
'Daring Do and the Curse
of the Pharaoh's Tomb'

03:51.931 --> 03:53.632
will be her last.

03:53.667 --> 03:56.568
Yearling looks forward
to her retirement."

03:56.603 --> 03:58.570
That doesn't
explain anything!

03:58.605 --> 03:59.938
[small groan]

03:59.973 --> 04:02.641
It just says you're
giving up writing stories.

04:02.676 --> 04:05.777
But most ponies don't know that
you actually are Daring Do

04:05.812 --> 04:07.579
and that the
stories are real.

04:07.614 --> 04:09.748
So what you're REALLY saying
is that you're giving up

04:09.783 --> 04:12.751
being Daring Do, but
you're not saying why!

04:12.786 --> 04:14.619
Of course, if you don't
feel like talking about it,

04:14.654 --> 04:16.988
that's A-OK, A.K.!

04:17.023 --> 04:19.858
As your friends, we
completely understand.

04:19.893 --> 04:22.460
Right, Rainbow Dash?

04:22.495 --> 04:25.964
Oh. Yeah. We just came to
make sure you're all right.

04:25.999 --> 04:29.334
That's really why we wanted
to find out what's going on.

04:29.369 --> 04:31.770
If you really
want to know...

04:31.805 --> 04:35.407
My last quest took me to a
village in Southern Equestria

04:35.442 --> 04:37.442
where I started seeing these.

04:38.678 --> 04:40.879
"WAKE OF DESTRUCTION:

04:40.914 --> 04:44.549
DARING DO RUINS ENTIRE
VILLAGE MARKETPLACE"!

04:44.584 --> 04:46.351
"DARE OR SCARE?

04:46.386 --> 04:50.355
LOCAL ROGUE 'DARING DO'
INVOLVED IN FRIGHTFUL FIASCO"?

04:50.390 --> 04:53.625
"DARING DO LEADS BULL INTO CHINA
SHOP DURING HIGH SPEED CHASE--"

04:53.660 --> 04:54.759
That's enough!

04:54.794 --> 04:56.428
[sigh]

04:56.463 --> 04:58.463
Everypony I tried to
help is mad at me.

04:58.498 --> 04:59.597
That's not true!

04:59.632 --> 05:00.899
They're not mad
at A.K. Yearling.

05:00.934 --> 05:03.401
They're mad at
"Daring Do".

05:03.436 --> 05:05.904
They don't sell my books
in Southern Equestria.

05:05.939 --> 05:09.407
The ponies there don't
know who A.K. Yearling is.

05:09.442 --> 05:11.743
They only know Daring Do

05:11.778 --> 05:15.046
and apparently she does
more harm than good.

05:15.081 --> 05:16.948
I guess it's a good thing
you look so different

05:16.983 --> 05:18.883
as A.K. Yearling!

05:18.918 --> 05:20.952
So all we have to
do is go down there

05:20.987 --> 05:23.788
and explain to these ponies that
none of this stuff is true.

05:23.823 --> 05:26.057
Easy-peazy-cheezy!

05:26.092 --> 05:28.393
But that's just the thing...

05:28.428 --> 05:29.794
it<u> is</u> true.

05:29.829 --> 05:31.496
WHAT?

05:31.531 --> 05:33.131
I guess I've always
been so focused

05:33.166 --> 05:35.967
on saving priceless relics
and stopping the bad guys

05:36.002 --> 05:39.571
that I never really thought
about the mess I leave behind.

05:39.606 --> 05:41.940
Then you ARE in
a tricky pickle.

05:41.975 --> 05:44.843
But why is all this
happening now?

05:44.878 --> 05:47.879
I guess ponies are
finally fed up.

05:47.914 --> 05:52.417
Either way, I'm done with
adventures: having or writing.

05:52.452 --> 05:53.752
Come on!

05:53.787 --> 05:55.520
For every one
pony who's upset,

05:55.555 --> 05:58.390
there must be at least a hundred
that know you're a hero.

05:58.425 --> 06:00.959
I don't think so, Dash.

06:00.994 --> 06:05.697
Well, why don't we go visit
this village "Somnambula"

06:05.732 --> 06:07.732
and see for ourselves?

06:07.767 --> 06:09.567
Those articles seem to
make it pretty clear

06:09.602 --> 06:11.436
how the villagers feel.

06:11.471 --> 06:14.072
But if we go there, the ponies
can tell you in person

06:14.107 --> 06:16.808
just how much they
appreciate you.

06:16.843 --> 06:19.911
And what a heap of rotten apple
cores these articles are!

06:21.648 --> 06:23.415
You really think so?

06:23.450 --> 06:24.816
I know so!

06:24.851 --> 06:25.917
Let's go!

06:27.587 --> 06:28.653
[sigh]

06:29.889 --> 06:41.866
♪♪

06:41.901 --> 06:43.968
This is so cool!

06:44.003 --> 06:46.504
It looks just like that
village in your last book

06:46.539 --> 06:48.506
where Daring Do recovers
the Doomed Diadem

06:48.541 --> 06:49.908
from The Wild Bunch Gang

06:49.943 --> 06:51.209
who chase after her
through the desert!

06:51.244 --> 06:52.811
It should.

06:52.846 --> 06:55.480
I based that entire chapter
on my experiences here

06:55.515 --> 06:56.881
in Somnambula.

06:56.916 --> 06:59.651
What happens? No
wait, don't tell me.

06:59.686 --> 07:01.553
I CHANGED MY MIND! TELL ME!

07:01.588 --> 07:04.489
Daring Do thwarts Ahuizotl's
evil plot to separate

07:04.524 --> 07:06.157
the Sister Crown Relics.

07:06.192 --> 07:08.860
And if it wasn't for her, the
region would be cursed

07:08.895 --> 07:12.230
with eternal night and the
entire town of Somnambula

07:12.265 --> 07:14.566
would have sunk
into the ground!

07:14.601 --> 07:16.901
Ah Pssht! There's no
chance that these ponies

07:16.936 --> 07:18.537
don't think you're a hero.

07:19.806 --> 07:21.106
Watch this.

07:22.909 --> 07:25.143
Hiya there, Mister!

07:25.178 --> 07:30.114
I was hoping you could tell me
about a pony named Daring Do.

07:30.149 --> 07:32.984
I hear she's an awesome
adventure-pony hero.

07:33.019 --> 07:34.152
Daring Do?

07:34.187 --> 07:37.589
Oh, she's awesome, all right.

07:37.624 --> 07:40.024
Awesome at destroying
ponies' apple carts

07:40.059 --> 07:41.259
[crash]

07:41.294 --> 07:43.228
and priceless,
sacred statues!

07:43.263 --> 07:45.797
♪♪

07:45.832 --> 07:48.566
Indeed. Daring
Do is a menace

07:48.601 --> 07:50.836
who destroys everything
she touches!

07:52.739 --> 07:54.005
[murmurs of agreement]

07:54.040 --> 07:55.640
What? No!

07:55.675 --> 07:58.243
Daring Do is the exact
opposite of a menace.

07:58.278 --> 08:01.212
I tried to tell you!

08:01.247 --> 08:02.848
Coming back here
was a mistake!

08:09.055 --> 08:09.988
♪♪

08:10.023 --> 08:13.024
Come on, A.K.! So we
picked a bad example.

08:13.059 --> 08:15.059
That was just one angry pony!

08:15.094 --> 08:16.828
Two angry ponies!

08:16.863 --> 08:18.229
It doesn't matter.

08:18.264 --> 08:20.098
I never should
have come with you!

08:20.133 --> 08:21.700
You two should just go home.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.937
Come on! We gotta
follow her!

08:25.972 --> 08:27.272
I dunno...

08:27.307 --> 08:29.207
it really seemed like
she doesn't want us

08:29.242 --> 08:31.576
cramping her saddle.

08:31.611 --> 08:35.046
But we have to convince her
that ponies do appreciate her!

08:35.081 --> 08:37.916
As her friend, I have to
make sure she believes that.

08:41.754 --> 08:44.722
Look, Pinkie! It's
the "Get On Inn".

08:44.757 --> 08:48.026
Daring Do stays here all
the time in her adventures.

08:48.061 --> 08:52.030
Which means there must be
ponies here who love Daring Do!

08:52.065 --> 08:53.298
Maybe they can help us.

08:53.333 --> 08:55.266
Mmmmm.

08:55.301 --> 08:59.070
My nose is telling me to
help myself to muffins.

08:59.105 --> 09:00.738
[ding]

09:00.773 --> 09:01.940
Come on.

09:03.977 --> 09:06.110
Ooo, she's fancy.

09:06.145 --> 09:07.612
I got this!

09:07.647 --> 09:10.114
A good evening
to you, Madame!

09:10.149 --> 09:13.251
We are but weary travelers who
humbly wish to inquire

09:13.286 --> 09:15.653
on the status of a
certain mare of intrigue

09:15.688 --> 09:17.655
taking residence here.

09:17.690 --> 09:20.858
What in Southern Equestria
are you on about?

09:20.893 --> 09:23.027
Is it true that
Daring Do stays here?

09:23.062 --> 09:25.763
Ha! Not anymore, she doesn't!

09:25.798 --> 09:27.732
Why not?

09:27.767 --> 09:30.301
The last time I rented
that rascal a room,

09:30.336 --> 09:32.770
she was in a such a rush to
high-tail it outta here,

09:32.805 --> 09:34.238
she didn't even pay her bill!

09:34.273 --> 09:37.375
But--
- After that, a band of
ruffians showed up

09:37.410 --> 09:39.611
and destroyed half the
rooms looking for her.

09:39.646 --> 09:42.780
Guess she made them even
more mad than she made me!

09:42.815 --> 09:44.849
No, no, no. You've
got it all wrong.

09:44.884 --> 09:46.918
How do ya figure?

09:46.953 --> 09:49.687
Daring Do was trying to
save everypony from the

09:49.722 --> 09:52.657
Curse of the Doomed
Diadem of Xilati!

09:52.692 --> 09:55.360
And she was only in a rush
because she had to get the crown

09:55.395 --> 09:59.664
back to the Tiara of Teotlale
before the curse took effect.

09:59.699 --> 10:01.699
Chapter seventeen.

10:01.734 --> 10:04.335
Sounds like a tall tale to me.

10:04.370 --> 10:06.904
And a hard one to believe now
that I know Daring Do

10:06.939 --> 10:10.775
is a scoundrel and a thief!

10:10.810 --> 10:14.379
Every year, ponies come to
offer precious glowpaz

10:14.414 --> 10:16.914
to the Sonmambula
statue in the village

10:16.949 --> 10:19.183
in hopes for a good future.

10:19.218 --> 10:21.986
Why that poor fella had
his glowpaz necklace

10:22.021 --> 10:25.223
stolen by Daring Do
just yesterday!

10:25.258 --> 10:26.391
Hmmmm.

10:27.994 --> 10:28.826
[gasp]

10:28.861 --> 10:29.928
THERE'S A.K.!

10:32.031 --> 10:36.768
Daring Do RUINED our town and
stole our precious glowpaz!

10:36.803 --> 10:39.737
We need to make sure that
if she turns up again,

10:39.772 --> 10:42.206
there will be consequences!

10:42.241 --> 10:46.210
Everypony who's with me,
meet at the statue tomorrow!

10:46.245 --> 10:48.246
[crowd agrees]

10:48.281 --> 10:50.915
Now I'm getting blamed for
things I didn't even do?

10:50.950 --> 10:52.817
Why would I steal from them?

10:52.852 --> 10:55.253
They are SUPER BAD!

10:55.288 --> 10:57.055
But... we're still
staying the night, right?

10:58.324 --> 11:01.325
Because I already ate all
the free mini muffins!

11:01.360 --> 11:04.462
Listen, A.K., after a
good night's sleep,

11:04.497 --> 11:06.197
we're going to fix
all of this.

11:06.232 --> 11:07.332
I promise.

11:11.437 --> 11:13.738
I shouldn't be
here, Rainbow Dash.

11:13.773 --> 11:15.206
This is never
going to work.

11:15.241 --> 11:17.341
Of course it will!

11:17.376 --> 11:20.278
All I have to do is go up
there and explain to everypony

11:20.313 --> 11:22.480
how wrong they all are.

11:22.515 --> 11:25.717
Yeah! And then I'll be
like what she said!

11:25.752 --> 11:28.453
Easy-peazy-cheezy.

11:28.488 --> 11:30.154
Exactly!

11:30.189 --> 11:32.323
Here it is! The
remains of your--

11:32.358 --> 11:35.760
I mean our
Somnambula statue.

11:35.795 --> 11:38.429
Now that Daring Do has
destroyed it, tell me...

11:38.464 --> 11:41.199
where will we hang our glowpaz?

11:41.234 --> 11:43.835
We don't even have any glowpaz
because they were stolen

11:43.870 --> 11:45.203
by Daring Do!

11:45.238 --> 11:50.007
[shouts of agreement]

11:50.042 --> 11:52.510
Daring Do would
never steal anything!

11:52.545 --> 11:55.279
And OK, she destroyed
your statue,

11:55.314 --> 11:57.315
but it was because she was
trying to save you all

11:57.350 --> 11:58.783
from Ahuizotl!

11:58.818 --> 12:01.486
[curious chatter]

12:01.521 --> 12:02.887
Ahuizotl?

12:02.922 --> 12:03.755
He's about yea big?

12:03.790 --> 12:04.388
Long neck?

12:04.423 --> 12:05.323
Itty-bitty face?

12:05.358 --> 12:06.424
Weird claw thingy on his tail?

12:08.194 --> 12:11.763
Ooo! Ooo! I know him!
He's a baddie.

12:11.798 --> 12:16.768
[concerned murmurs]

12:16.803 --> 12:19.771
Trust me, if Ahuizotl had gotten
away with the Doomed Diadem,

12:19.806 --> 12:22.206
your entire village would
have been swallowed up!

12:22.241 --> 12:25.443
And that's a lot worse than
losing some CRUMMY old statue!

12:25.478 --> 12:26.778
[gasp]

12:26.813 --> 12:28.146
Ahem!

12:28.181 --> 12:31.082
This was not some
crummy old statue.

12:31.117 --> 12:33.251
It was the namesake
of our town.

12:33.286 --> 12:37.188
If you want to understand us,
you must first understand her.

12:37.223 --> 12:38.156
Who?

12:38.191 --> 12:39.891
Somnambula...

12:39.926 --> 12:44.562
<i>Long ago this village fell</i>
<i>prey to an evil Sphinx</i>

12:44.597 --> 12:47.465
<i>who demanded most</i>
<i>of their crops.</i>

12:47.500 --> 12:52.136
<i>Like her fellow villagers,</i>
<i>Somnambula didn't have much,</i>

12:52.171 --> 12:56.440
<i>but she used what she had to</i>
<i>keep others from giving up hope.</i>

12:56.475 --> 12:59.510
<i>The son of the</i>
<i>Pharaoh, Prince Hisan,</i>

12:59.545 --> 13:01.913
<i>was so moved by</i>
<i>her compassion,</i>

13:01.948 --> 13:05.383
<i>that he decreed nopony</i>
<i>would go hungry again.</i>

13:05.418 --> 13:12.190
♪♪

13:12.225 --> 13:15.259
<i>But when Hisan stood</i>
<i>up to the Sphinx,</i>

13:15.294 --> 13:19.363
<i>the beast captured him, telling</i>
<i>the Pharaoh the only way</i>

13:19.398 --> 13:23.367
<i>to get Hisan back was to</i>
<i>solve her riddle.</i>

13:23.402 --> 13:26.537
<i>Nopony would volunteer</i>
<i>to save the prince.</i>

13:26.572 --> 13:29.874
<i>Nopony except Somnambula.</i>

13:29.909 --> 13:36.347
<i>♪♪</i>

13:36.382 --> 13:39.150
<i>The Sphinx gave her the riddle,</i>

13:39.185 --> 13:45.022
<i>"I shine brightest in the dark.</i>
<i>I am there but cannot be seen.</i>

13:45.057 --> 13:47.258
<i>To have me costs you nothing.</i>

13:47.293 --> 13:51.362
<i>To be without me costs</i>
<i>you everything."</i>

13:51.397 --> 13:53.531
<i>As Somnambula thought</i>
<i>of the hardship</i>

13:53.566 --> 13:56.901
<i>she and her fellow</i>
<i>villagers had experienced,</i>

13:56.936 --> 13:59.036
<i>she instantly</i>
<i>knew the answer.</i>

13:59.071 --> 13:59.971
<i>"HOPE!"</i>

14:00.006 --> 14:01.405
<i>She shouted.</i>

14:01.440 --> 14:03.407
[roar]

14:03.442 --> 14:05.877
<i>The Sphinx was so enraged, it</i>
<i>seemed she might still refuse</i>

14:05.912 --> 14:07.411
<i>to release the prince,</i>

14:07.446 --> 14:11.215
<i>so Somnambula asked her</i>
<i>for one more challenge,</i>

14:11.250 --> 14:13.084
<i>but if she</i>
<i>accomplished it,</i>

14:13.119 --> 14:16.654
<i>the Sphinx would leave</i>
<i>from the kingdom forever.</i>

14:16.689 --> 14:18.456
<i>The Sphinx quickly agreed,</i>

14:18.491 --> 14:21.659
<i>asking only that Somnambula</i>
<i>walk to the prince...</i>

14:21.694 --> 14:26.197
<i>... across a deep</i>
<i>chasm, blindfolded!</i>

14:26.232 --> 14:29.500
<i>Further, the Sphinx had</i>
<i>cast a powerful spell</i>

14:29.535 --> 14:32.003
<i>that prevented</i>
<i>Somnambula from flying.</i>

14:32.038 --> 14:33.238
<i>[evil laugh]</i>

14:35.141 --> 14:38.309
<i>But Somnambula never lost HOPE!</i>

14:38.344 --> 14:40.378
<i>She knew she'd need to</i>
<i>make a leap of faith</i>

14:40.413 --> 14:42.914
<i>to save the</i> prince.

14:42.949 --> 14:45.416
<i>Guided by the sound</i>
<i>of the prince's voice...</i>

14:48.487 --> 14:51.322
<i>she easily made it across.</i>

14:51.357 --> 14:52.456
[roar]

14:52.491 --> 14:55.159
♪♪

14:58.731 --> 15:01.933
<i>The Pharaoh asked how</i>
<i>Somnambula prevailed</i>

15:01.968 --> 15:04.502
<i>and she explained that</i>
<i>she had always hoped</i>

15:04.537 --> 15:07.305
<i>she could make things</i>
<i>better for her people</i>

15:07.340 --> 15:10.508
<i>and that hope</i>
<i>had carried her through.</i>

15:10.543 --> 15:13.711
<i>The Prince replaced the</i>
<i>pearls Somnambula gave up</i>

15:13.746 --> 15:16.347
<i>with a string of Glowpaz.</i>

15:16.382 --> 15:19.650
<i>And around her neck, they</i>
<i>glowed bright enough</i>

15:19.685 --> 15:23.020
<i>to light the entire kingdom.</i>

15:23.055 --> 15:27.692
<i>Forever after, Glowpaz</i>
<i>became our symbol of hope.</i>

15:30.062 --> 15:34.432
Wow. I had no idea how special
the statue was to you.

15:34.467 --> 15:37.101
Somnambula sounds like
a pretty cool pony.

15:37.136 --> 15:38.736
But I bet if she were here,

15:38.771 --> 15:41.372
she'd tell you how cool
Daring Do is too

15:41.407 --> 15:43.374
because they've both
fought to protect this town!

15:43.409 --> 15:46.077
[chattering]

15:46.112 --> 15:49.347
If Somnambula were here today,
she would condemn Daring Do

15:49.382 --> 15:52.717
for destroying yo--
OUR symbol of hope!

15:52.752 --> 15:57.421
[booing and shouts]

15:57.456 --> 15:59.757
♪♪

16:03.629 --> 16:07.231
♪♪

16:07.266 --> 16:08.332
Hey, buddy!

16:08.367 --> 16:11.535
What did Daring Do ever do
to you to deserve all this?

16:11.570 --> 16:14.338
Only... everything!

16:14.373 --> 16:16.474
Dr. Caballeron?

16:16.509 --> 16:19.710
Yes... Rainbow Dash.

16:19.745 --> 16:22.079
[nasty laugh]

16:22.114 --> 16:25.016
When I saw you,
her closest friend,

16:25.051 --> 16:27.785
I knew that Daring Do
would not be far behind.

16:27.820 --> 16:31.589
I really do owe you for
leading her right to me.

16:31.624 --> 16:33.057
But I didn't mean--

16:33.092 --> 16:35.659
Thank you for helping me
break Daring Do's spirit

16:35.694 --> 16:37.561
by destroying
her reputation,

16:37.596 --> 16:41.065
but I can't have you running
off and telling her my plan.

16:41.100 --> 16:42.199
[whistle]

16:42.234 --> 16:46.737
♪♪

16:46.772 --> 16:48.239
HELP!

16:49.742 --> 16:51.042
Caballeron?

16:51.077 --> 16:52.309
No!

16:52.344 --> 16:53.544
He's got Rainbow Dash!

16:53.579 --> 16:54.479
Come on!

16:59.351 --> 17:00.718
[panting]

17:00.753 --> 17:05.189
I'm... coming...
Rainbow... Dash...

17:06.826 --> 17:08.459
I knew you'd come!

17:08.494 --> 17:09.460
You did?

17:09.495 --> 17:10.795
I sure didn't.

17:10.830 --> 17:12.596
What if I cause
more trouble?

17:12.631 --> 17:13.564
You won't.

17:13.599 --> 17:14.632
How do you know?

17:14.667 --> 17:16.167
I just do!

17:16.202 --> 17:18.135
You wouldn't let anything
happen to Rainbow Dash.

17:18.170 --> 17:20.104
You care too much.

17:20.139 --> 17:21.238
You're right.

17:21.273 --> 17:22.340
Which way did they go?

17:26.145 --> 17:27.145
To the pyramid!

17:28.447 --> 17:30.314
Dash: Somepony help!

17:31.750 --> 17:34.652
Somepony! Anypony!

17:34.687 --> 17:36.487
Pinkie Pie! Daring Do!

17:36.522 --> 17:37.755
Is that you?

17:37.790 --> 17:39.123
Don't worry, Rainbow!

17:39.158 --> 17:40.724
We'll save you!

17:40.759 --> 17:42.460
[rumbling]

17:42.495 --> 17:44.361
[gurgling]

17:44.396 --> 17:47.431
[evil laugh]

17:47.466 --> 17:50.835
If my previous plan didn't cause
you to give up, Daring Do,

17:50.870 --> 17:54.238
then the shame of losing your
dear friend Rainbow Dash

17:54.273 --> 17:56.140
to the slime will!

17:57.676 --> 18:02.513
Oh, and that ancient magic
from the legend is real.

18:02.548 --> 18:05.282
There'll be no flying
in the pyramid!

18:05.317 --> 18:07.218
Good luck, Daring Do!

18:07.253 --> 18:08.853
[laughter]

18:09.688 --> 18:10.521
[slam]

18:14.660 --> 18:17.828
He's right! We'll never
get to her in time!

18:17.863 --> 18:20.264
If this really is like
Somnambula's story,

18:20.299 --> 18:22.733
then we just have to
have hope that we can!

18:22.768 --> 18:25.136
I think we need more
than hope, Pinkie.

18:25.171 --> 18:27.605
There was a bridge in the story
and there's no bridge here.

18:27.640 --> 18:29.206
What are we going to do?

18:29.241 --> 18:31.308
[moans]

18:31.343 --> 18:33.844
I don't know, but Rainbow
Dash is our friend!

18:33.879 --> 18:36.847
Just like Somnambula. We
need to make a leap of faith

18:36.882 --> 18:38.549
and hope that we can save her!

18:39.652 --> 18:40.618
PINKIE!

18:46.725 --> 18:47.858
Wheeee!

18:47.893 --> 18:48.926
Hee hee hee!

18:48.961 --> 18:50.895
♪♪

18:50.930 --> 18:53.164
I knew we'd do it!

18:53.199 --> 18:55.833
Thanks for reminding me to
never give up hope, Pinkie.

18:55.868 --> 18:58.836
And I'm kinda hoping you
ponies will untie me

18:58.871 --> 19:01.606
before we all take a bath
in bubbling green slime!

19:03.976 --> 19:05.309
We're on it!

19:05.344 --> 19:11.749
♪♪

19:21.927 --> 19:23.794
Not so fast, Caballeron!

19:28.234 --> 19:30.367
YOU stole our glowpaz!

19:30.402 --> 19:33.971
[angry shouts]

19:34.006 --> 19:36.974
I should have known you were
just trying to sully my name

19:37.009 --> 19:39.977
so that you'd be free to
steal whatever you wanted.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.680
Of course that was
the plan, Daring Do!

19:42.715 --> 19:45.516
At first I just
wanted the Glowpaz...

19:45.551 --> 19:50.321
But then I saw an opportunity to
write you out of the story

19:50.356 --> 19:52.623
FOR GOOD!

19:52.658 --> 19:54.592
[gasps]

19:54.627 --> 19:58.295
And with the destruction
you leave in your wake,

19:58.330 --> 20:00.497
it didn't take too much
to convince ponies

20:00.532 --> 20:02.700
you were a villain.

20:02.735 --> 20:04.902
You're wrong, Caballeron.

20:04.937 --> 20:07.471
And I won't let you
break my spirit again.

20:07.506 --> 20:09.740
Because I'm never
going to give up hope

20:09.775 --> 20:12.409
that I can protect ponies
and ancient treasures

20:12.444 --> 20:14.745
from miscreants like you!

20:14.780 --> 20:16.847
[agreeing shouts]

20:16.882 --> 20:20.017
Remember! She
ruined your statue!

20:20.052 --> 20:21.852
You're fools to
believe in her!

20:25.324 --> 20:29.693
You'll pay for this, Daring Do!

20:29.728 --> 20:34.331
[cheers]

20:34.366 --> 20:35.466
OK, OK that's enough!

20:37.903 --> 20:40.304
Thanks for helping
me come to my senses.

20:40.339 --> 20:41.905
You two are true friends.

20:41.940 --> 20:43.040
Are you kidding?

20:43.075 --> 20:43.641
That.

20:43.676 --> 20:44.608
Was.

20:44.643 --> 20:46.510
Awesome!

20:46.545 --> 20:48.979
We're just glad you're back
to your old self again!

20:49.014 --> 20:51.582
[giggle] Me too!

20:51.617 --> 20:53.617
But I'm glad I realized that
even if you're fighting

20:53.652 --> 20:57.788
for something good, you're still
responsible for your actions.

20:57.823 --> 21:00.958
And if something bad happens
that you didn't intend,

21:00.993 --> 21:04.061
you shouldn't give up hope
or lose faith in yourself.

21:04.096 --> 21:07.965
Yeah! All ya gotta do
is make it right.

21:08.000 --> 21:10.034
Feel free to use that
in your next book!

21:10.069 --> 21:12.603
You know, I think I will.

21:12.638 --> 21:16.807
[squeals]

21:16.842 --> 21:22.012
♪♪

21:22.047 --> 21:23.380
[ding]

21:23.415 --> 21:28.452
♪♪

21:28.487 --> 21:30.354
[cheers]
